This paper deals with software patches and their accompanying log messages, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed model, CC2Vec, is a neural network that learns a representation of code changes, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also uses attention mechanisms and comparison functions, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
